family_en_des:
NetBus is a famous and widely used backdoor that natively supports Windows NT Series of operating systems. It is usually combined by attackers with Back Orifice to make the attack. 
NetBus is not a virus, but believed as a Trojan. It is widely used to steal data and delete data. NetBus allows attackers to read data and remotely control some Windows functions. The server of NetBus in installed in the remote system with the aim for storage. The NetBus server V1.6 is a Windows PE file named PATCH.EXE. The sever installs itself in the Windows directory and run in an automatic way when Windows starts next time. 
NetBus is Trojan similar to BackOrifice. It will open a backdoor in the host and make everyone whose computer is connected to the Internet easily access the infected computer. Then the attacker is able to click your mouse, open your video, run the CD-ROM and even delete your files. It is very convenient and powerful for NetBus to control the NT. First appeared in March 1998, two recent versions are V1.60 and V1.70. 
The NetBus client is netbus.exe and the server is patch.exe. The control of a remote computer requires the installation of the client in it. This is realized by executing the NetBus Trojan by the computer user unintentionally. 
There are many ways to find and delete NetBus. Usually, the server program is installed in Windows system directory and auto-run when the system starts. If NetBus is installed in a hidden way via a game named whackamole.exe, then the server name will be explore.exe (Note: it is not explorer.exe!) or game.exe. Meanwhile, an user can check the Windows registry key. NetBus adds its own StarUp in the following path: \\HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINESOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run by which NetBus is able to auto-run when Windows starts. Even you click Ctrl+Alt+Del, its process can be seen in the task list. 
The correct removal approach is listed below:
1. run regedit.ext;
2. find \\HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINESOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run;
3. delete patch or explore related contents;
4. reboot the computer and delete patch.exe or explore.exe in the Windows system directory.

family_cn_des:
Backdoor.Win32.Xtreme家族是一个恶意后门程序家族，因此他是基于特定行为命名的家族                       Xtreme运行后,会从自身资源中解密出有关配置文件，然后按照配置文件中的相关参数设置一步一步执行后续操作。该恶意后门程序还会注入一些进程文件,诸如:svchost.exe和iexplore.exe进程，并且主动连接互联网络中指定的Web服务器，使用动态域名解析服务连接远程恶意攻击者的计算机系统，使其可以远程操控受感染的操作系统。
　　另外,该恶意后门程序入侵计算机系统后，迫使受感染操作系统执行如下操作:
　　1、 下载执行任意文件、上传文件至互联网络中的FTP服务器;
　　2、 利用移动存储介质等进行传播、进行键盘记录、窃取操作系统中私密数据信息;
　　3、 修改系统设置、运行或结束操作系统中的应用程序或者安装其他木马、病毒插件并自动进行更新操作。

